HEADWORD: ilama
<hw>ilama</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A tropical American tree
(<spn>Annona diversifolia</spn>) grown in the southern U. S. having a
whitish pink-tinged fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ilama tree, <spn>Annona
diversifolia</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>whitish tropical fruit with a pinkish tinge related
to custard apples, grown in the southern U. S.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

